Congenital hepatic fibrosis, cystic kidneys, mental retardation, and facial dysmorphy: a new report of an autosomal recessive syndrome. This report concerns a boy with congenital hepatic fibrosis, cystic kidneys, mental retardation, and minor dysmorphic features. These symptoms have rarely been reported before and indicate that congenital hepatic fibrosis may not be a single clinical entity.